# Security Header Checker

A Python-based web security tool that checks whether a website implements important HTTP security headers.

## Features

* Checks Content-Security-Policy (CSP)
* Checks X-Frame-Options
* Checks X-Content-Type-Options
* Checks Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS)
* Checks Referrer-Policy
* Checks Permissions-Policy
* Simple and beginner-friendly

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/security-header-checker.git
cd security-header-checker
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Usage

Run the script:

```bash
python header_checker.py
```

Enter a website URL when prompted:

```text
Enter website URL (https://...): https://example.com
```

Example output:

```text
Checking security headers for https://example.com

[FOUND] Content-Security-Policy
[FOUND] X-Frame-Options
[MISSING] Strict-Transport-Security
[MISSING] Permissions-Policy
```

